<!-- About -->
<section class="section section--about" id="about">
  <div class="section__header">
    <div class="label">About</div>
    <h2 class="section__title reveal">A bit about me</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="about-grid">
    <div class="about__text reveal reveal--clip">
      <p>
        I get excited about the moment something complicated suddenly clicks — when a confusing flow
        becomes obvious, or when an AI response actually sounds like it's listening.
        That's what I spend most of my days doing at <strong>VRT MAX</strong>, Flanders' public broadcaster,
        where I design the streaming experience as a UX consultant via <strong>iO</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Before that, I spent two years designing 186 conversations for <a href="/portfolio/kate-kbc/">Kate, the digital
        assistant inside <strong>KBC</strong>'s banking app</a> — and was the first designer to explore integrating LLMs into what
        was then a fully rule-based chatbot. The result? A world's best banking app award
        and Belgium's best chatbot. I also gave a
        <a href="https://youtu.be/mpPM_u8sM_w" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">talk at UX Beers</a> about that exact transition.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside client work, I'm a board member at <strong>Open Knowledge Belgium</strong>
        and coordinate the <strong>Open Summer of Code</strong>, where students build real
        open-source civic tech in four weeks flat.
      </p>
      <p>
        I also run <strong>Valderas</strong>, where I help companies like <strong>Nitra</strong>
        get their operations unstuck — CRM workflows, marketing automations, the kind of
        behind-the-scenes tooling nobody sees but everyone relies on.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="about__details reveal">
      <div class="about__detail-group">
        <div class="label">Currently</div>
        <ul class="about__list">
          <li>UX Designer, VRT MAX — via iO</li>
          <li>Design & Strategy — Valderas</li>
          <li>Board Member — Open Knowledge Belgium</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="about__detail-group">
